<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<pageBreakToken pageId="39" pageNumber="40" start="start">Remarks</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, ALM" journalOrPublisher="Annales du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="115 - 129" title="Memoire sur quelques especes nouvelles d'insectes de la section des Hymenopteres appeles les Portetuyaux, et sur les caracteres de cette famille et des genres qui la composent." volume="7" year="1806">Lepeletier (1806)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum caerulescens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulescens">Hedychrum caerulescens</taxonomicName>
based on two specimens, one male and one female. One of these two syntypes was acquired by Spinola and belongs to the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ashmead, 1902" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Pseudomalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudomalus violaceus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violaceus">Pseudomalus violaceus</taxonomicName>
(Scopoli, 1763); the second syntype is housed at MNHN. Du 
<bibRefCitation author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="518 - 580" title="Etude des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="66" year="1898">Buysson (1898</bibRefCitation>
: 563) listed one specimen in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lepeletier’s">Lepeletier's</normalizedToken>
collection 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum coerulescens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coerulescens">Hedychrum coerulescens</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Ellampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ellampus caeruleus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleus">Ellampus caeruleus</taxonomicName>
(De Geer), but it is not listed as a type. We examined the second syntype (currently in the general collection MNHN box 8). It belongs to the same species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ashmead, 1902" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Pseudomalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudomalus violaceus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violaceus">Pseudomalus violaceus</taxonomicName>
(Scopoli), even though it is placed under the name of 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omalus aeneus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">Omalus aeneus</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
We designate as lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum caerulescens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulescens">Hedychrum caerulescens</taxonomicName>
Lepeletier the syntype male. The reason is to fix the synonym with 
<taxonomicName authority="Ashmead, 1902" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Pseudomalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudomalus violaceus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violaceus">Pseudomalus violaceus</taxonomicName>
(Scopoli). The specimen is damaged, lacking its fore wings and left hind wing, and it is partially covered by mould.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="current status">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Current status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName authority="Ashmead, 1902" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Pseudomalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudomalus violaceus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violaceus">Pseudomalus violaceus</taxonomicName>
(Scopoli, 1763) (synonymised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalla Torre, CG" journalOrPublisher="Engelmann, Lipsiae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Chrysididae (Tubulifera). Tip. G." year="1892">Dalla Torre 1892</bibRefCitation>
: 19; transferred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="University Press, New York" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart 1991</bibRefCitation>
: 270).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
